cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the task of embedding entire graphs, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and graph kernels suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The mention of "task-independent algorithms" and "unsupervised learning" suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
